WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.878
♪

00:02.878 --> 00:04.880
CHARLES-HADEN SAVAGE:
What do we know? Bunny was killed

00:04.880 --> 00:05.881
with a knitting needle

00:06.924 --> 00:07.966
and a knife.

00:08.675 --> 00:09.927
What did happen that night?

00:09.927 --> 00:11.470
MABEL MORA:
It's all a blur.

00:11.470 --> 00:14.389
- Memory can contain
both objective reality

00:14.389 --> 00:15.849
and subjective perception.

00:15.849 --> 00:18.143
- Everyone's just so obsessed
with my past.

00:18.143 --> 00:21.146
My dad got me a jigsaw puzzle
when I was 4.

00:21.146 --> 00:22.397
It was 1,000 pieces.

00:22.397 --> 00:23.649
- My DNA came back.

00:23.649 --> 00:25.359
Half was clearly Mom,

00:25.359 --> 00:27.736
but the other half was Greek.

00:27.736 --> 00:29.905
- I'm the only one who's been looking out

00:29.905 --> 00:31.490
for your interest!

00:32.616 --> 00:34.076
- I have no life anymore!

00:34.076 --> 00:35.160
- Where is Detective Williams?

00:35.160 --> 00:37.454
- She's on maternity leave in Denver.

00:37.454 --> 00:39.206
- We're texting with the killer!

00:39.206 --> 00:41.166
CHARLES: We tell him
we'll put the matchbook inside

00:41.166 --> 00:43.293
a Stop and Shop bag in a trash can

00:43.293 --> 00:44.253
outside Morningside Park.

00:44.253 --> 00:45.754
OLIVER PUTNAM: Glitter!
[pop]

00:45.754 --> 00:47.673
There's no getting rid of glitter.
- Fuck!

00:49.258 --> 00:51.635
There goes our best chance
at clearing our names.

00:52.219 --> 00:55.013
MAN: [on video]
Yo! Bloody Mabel sighting number two!

00:55.013 --> 00:56.431
She just stabbed some dude!

00:57.641 --> 01:00.644
♪

01:01.353 --> 01:03.355
MABEL:
My dad loved puzzles.

01:06.608 --> 01:08.861
Especially the ones
with lots of pieces

01:08.861 --> 01:11.029
that could swallow up
an entire weekend.

01:13.240 --> 01:14.741
After he'd moved out,

01:14.741 --> 01:17.327
the two of us got into this routine.

01:17.327 --> 01:20.330
Every Sunday,
we'd sit around in our pajamas

01:20.330 --> 01:21.790
and do a puzzle together.

01:21.790 --> 01:23.458
- How long do you think
it'll take us this time?

01:23.458 --> 01:24.793
- A thousand years.
[laughs]

01:24.793 --> 01:26.545
- Well, your mom comes
to get you at 3:00,

01:26.545 --> 01:27.963
so we're gonna have
to do better than that.

01:27.963 --> 01:29.381
- I'm kidding. This one's easy.

01:29.840 --> 01:31.508
- Oh, yeah? Well, what if

01:31.508 --> 01:32.759
we do it without the box?

01:33.927 --> 01:35.554
No pictures to help us.

01:35.554 --> 01:37.097
- Still easy.

01:37.931 --> 01:41.685
MABEL'S FATHER: What if we do it
upside down then? Just the shapes.

01:41.685 --> 01:43.228
You think you can do it?
[Mabel scoffs]

01:52.404 --> 01:55.407
♪ mysterious music ♪

02:01.496 --> 02:04.208
[fan whooshing]

02:14.051 --> 02:17.054
[subway rumbling]

02:33.820 --> 02:35.697
[footsteps]
[keys jingling]

02:35.697 --> 02:38.867
[door unlocking]

02:38.867 --> 02:39.868
[door creaks]

02:51.588 --> 02:53.173
[grunts]

02:53.173 --> 02:54.174
[groans]

02:54.174 --> 02:55.467
- Of course, it's you!

02:55.467 --> 02:57.719
No! Stay back, asshole!
[mouthing]

03:01.807 --> 03:03.809
What? What are you saying?

03:06.186 --> 03:09.439
[video playing]
[crowd screaming]

03:11.108 --> 03:14.111
[screaming continues]

03:14.486 --> 03:17.072
WOMAN: [on video]
She stabbed him! She fucking stabbed him!

03:17.072 --> 03:18.574
MABEL:
Is that me?

03:20.868 --> 03:22.911
Did I stab someone...

03:22.911 --> 03:24.371
[screaming continues]

03:25.622 --> 03:27.040
...again?

03:28.125 --> 03:31.128
♪ lively theme song playing ♪

03:31.128 --> 03:34.131
♪ vocalizing ♪

04:14.171 --> 04:16.089
♪

04:16.089 --> 04:17.591
[soda can opens]

04:23.931 --> 04:25.807
[door shuts]
OLIVER: Okay. Okay.

04:25.807 --> 04:28.268
So, I-I checked out the Pickle Diner,
the subway stop,

04:28.268 --> 04:31.230
the SoHo Forever 21 just to be sure.
She's nowhere.

04:31.230 --> 04:33.315
- I called all the hospitals.
The only Mabel I found

04:33.315 --> 04:34.816
was 99 and had just died.

04:34.816 --> 04:36.443
I'm worried about her, Oliver.

04:36.443 --> 04:39.613
She hasn't answered any of my calls
or my text communications.

04:39.613 --> 04:41.406
- Nor mine. Which is extra concerning

04:41.406 --> 04:42.950
'cause we're always texting.

04:42.950 --> 04:45.452
The memes, Charles.
You should see the memes.

04:45.452 --> 04:46.954
[knocking]
- Mabel.

04:49.248 --> 04:50.749
[baby crying]

04:50.749 --> 04:51.834
OLIVER: Oh great.

04:51.834 --> 04:53.335
Now we have a baby to deal with.

04:54.545 --> 04:55.838
- Oh, it's not a baby.

04:56.880 --> 04:58.215
It's my trainee.

04:58.215 --> 05:00.467
Junior Detective Keith. You know what?

05:00.467 --> 05:01.802
Actually, y'all will get along,

05:01.802 --> 05:04.012
considering all you do is piss
your pants every 10 minutes.

05:04.847 --> 05:07.015
I need to talk to you. I got questions.

05:07.015 --> 05:09.184
[Keith crying]

05:09.184 --> 05:12.187
♪

05:12.813 --> 05:14.439
- Can I get you anything?

05:20.028 --> 05:21.905
- Nice accessory.

05:23.490 --> 05:25.701
You steal jewelry from dead people,

05:25.701 --> 05:28.328
and the state gives you an anklet.

05:28.328 --> 05:29.371
Kind of poetic.

05:29.913 --> 05:31.290
[slams mug]

05:34.418 --> 05:36.086
Did I really stab someone?

05:39.214 --> 05:41.508
You should be a trauma counselor,
Theo. Really.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.596
I don't know ASL.

05:46.180 --> 05:47.973
[sighs]
[pen clicks]

05:58.150 --> 05:59.943
No. Nothing.

06:00.944 --> 06:02.279
It's just gone.

06:11.914 --> 06:14.082
You can only get a third
of what I'm saying?

06:16.543 --> 06:19.588
It always seems like people
can lip read more in movies.

06:24.259 --> 06:26.094
Okay, I have to go.

06:26.094 --> 06:27.596
Do you know where my bag is?

06:27.596 --> 06:28.597
My bag.

06:29.139 --> 06:30.390
It had a matchbook

06:30.390 --> 06:32.351
with a bloody fingerprint on it.

06:33.060 --> 06:36.146
No, no! Theo,
th-that was our biggest clue!

06:38.357 --> 06:40.692
I don't-- I don't know what you're saying!
It has to be here!

06:44.321 --> 06:47.491
Theo, I still don't know ASL!
Why am I even here?

06:47.491 --> 06:48.492
[sighs]

06:51.912 --> 06:54.915
♪

06:54.915 --> 06:57.417
[muffled rumbling]

06:59.628 --> 07:02.047
[muffled banging]

07:02.589 --> 07:05.092
[pen scribbling]

07:05.092 --> 07:07.261
[muffled banging]

07:10.430 --> 07:14.184
[muffled]

07:19.481 --> 07:22.609
[muffled, distorted]
She stabbed him! She fucking stabbed him!

07:31.910 --> 07:33.912
He took my bag? Why...

07:35.622 --> 07:36.832
Was it Glitter Guy?

07:37.457 --> 07:38.917
The person on the train.

07:39.376 --> 07:41.920
Glitter Guy.
Did he have glitter on him?

07:46.049 --> 07:48.051
Is that ASL for "glitter"?

07:48.719 --> 07:50.888
That was kind of fun.

07:50.888 --> 07:51.889
- Uh...

07:56.894 --> 07:58.061
- Is this his?

07:58.770 --> 08:00.772
I need to get to Coney Island now.

08:02.316 --> 08:05.152
Not to stab him again.
Although, I'm leaving my options open.

08:05.152 --> 08:07.404
He has the matchbook,
and if he works there,

08:07.404 --> 08:09.573
they have to have
some kind of record or photos.

08:12.910 --> 08:15.579
No, no, no. I'm not letting you help me.

08:15.579 --> 08:16.747
You killed Zoe,

08:16.747 --> 08:19.499
and you let Oscar
sit in jail for 10 years.

08:21.919 --> 08:24.922
♪

08:35.682 --> 08:38.519
[street chatter]

08:38.519 --> 08:39.937
- So, what really happened

08:39.937 --> 08:41.813
when Mabel went to get
some more champagne that night?

08:42.397 --> 08:43.815
- Aren't you supposed to be in Denver?

08:43.815 --> 08:45.108
- Were you aware of her violent past?

08:45.108 --> 08:48.070
- Because we heard you were
in Denver on maternity leave.

08:48.070 --> 08:50.614
- Goddammit, would y'all focus?

08:50.614 --> 08:52.157
Yes.

08:52.157 --> 08:54.493
I was on a trip, as of last night,

08:54.493 --> 08:56.995
and I cut the shit short because there's
something that's been bothering me.

08:56.995 --> 08:58.247
It's been keeping me up at night.

08:58.247 --> 09:00.290
- Let me guess, it was your baby?
WILLIAMS: No!

09:00.290 --> 09:01.500
It was you, dipshits!

09:01.500 --> 09:03.627
I can't stop thinking
about this damn case,

09:03.627 --> 09:06.505
and how you clearly know things
that you're not sharing.

09:08.340 --> 09:09.341
CHARLES:
Hm?

09:11.093 --> 09:12.344
WILLIAMS:
Oh, okay.

09:12.344 --> 09:14.721
So it's gonna be like that?

09:14.721 --> 09:16.849
Because if you don't clear
some stuff up for me,

09:16.849 --> 09:19.101
I have no choice but to agree

09:19.101 --> 09:21.895
with a way less fuckin' friendly
Detective Kreps.

09:21.895 --> 09:25.190
Two stabbings with knitting needles?

09:25.190 --> 09:26.608
Come on, guys.

09:26.608 --> 09:29.403
That does not look good for your girl.
CHARLES: Hold on.

09:29.403 --> 09:32.030
Those are two unrelated incidents.

09:32.030 --> 09:34.283
Bunny was killed with a knife,
not a knitting needle,

09:34.283 --> 09:37.703
or did Detective Kreps
conveniently forget that?

09:37.703 --> 09:39.413
There is no knife here!

09:39.413 --> 09:42.666
And you won't find one at Mabel's either.
And you can turn Oliver's place

09:42.666 --> 09:44.835
upside down for all I care

09:44.835 --> 09:46.503
because you'd be wasting your time!

09:46.503 --> 09:48.839
Because Mabel didn't do it!
There you go.

09:50.507 --> 09:52.509
- Excuse me. I need...

09:53.677 --> 09:55.846
bathroom. I-I need to go to the bathroom.

09:56.680 --> 09:58.682
[heavy breathing, snorts]

10:00.184 --> 10:02.352
[door opens, shuts]
[baby cooing]

10:05.564 --> 10:08.066
[muffled]:
Ah! Open!

10:08.066 --> 10:11.153
[struggling] You... damned...

10:11.153 --> 10:12.696
[groans]

10:12.696 --> 10:14.239
Passageway! Oh!

10:14.239 --> 10:16.074
- Yo, is he okay?

10:18.076 --> 10:19.995
- You know-- [clears throat]

10:19.995 --> 10:22.831
I'm sure it's nothing.
He has an unorthodox diet.

10:22.831 --> 10:25.167
[nervous laugh]
So, you know what?

10:25.167 --> 10:28.879
I'm just gonna go, uh,
check on him. [laughs]

10:32.508 --> 10:34.051
[groans, gasps]

10:34.760 --> 10:35.761
[Oliver grunts]

10:36.512 --> 10:38.013
- Oh. Okay...

10:38.805 --> 10:39.806
Okay.

10:40.599 --> 10:41.808
- [whispers]:
Stop!

10:43.018 --> 10:44.561
Are you doing
what I think you're doing?

10:44.561 --> 10:46.522
- [whispers]:
Of course not!

10:46.522 --> 10:47.523
What do you think I'm doing?

10:47.523 --> 10:49.942
- You're sneaking into your apartment
to get rid of the bloody knife

10:49.942 --> 10:51.735
you should have gotten rid of ages ago!

10:51.735 --> 10:53.028
- Wrong.

10:53.028 --> 10:54.238
It was only days ago.

10:54.696 --> 10:56.990
You still have the murder weapon?
- Hey,

10:56.990 --> 10:59.785
buddy, if you don't like
the way I do my felonies,

10:59.785 --> 11:01.703
[muffled]
you're welcome to commit some yourself.

11:02.955 --> 11:03.956
[sighs]

11:05.374 --> 11:07.876
Okay. Okay. I'm sorry.

11:08.877 --> 11:11.213
[sighs] I-I forgot.

11:12.130 --> 11:14.925
- Forgot.
- I brought it with me to Jersey

11:14.925 --> 11:17.177
because, well, Jersey seems
like the place you go

11:17.177 --> 11:18.887
if you want to get rid of
incriminating evidence.

11:19.429 --> 11:22.975
But then, I got distracted
by an even bigger emergency.

11:23.350 --> 11:25.310
My son Will's production of Oz.

11:25.310 --> 11:27.563
I mean, talk about a disaster.

11:27.563 --> 11:29.314
But here's the good news.
- Finally.

11:29.314 --> 11:31.942
- I saved the show.

11:31.942 --> 11:34.069
It actually turned out pretty good.

11:34.069 --> 11:36.363
Will is over the moon.

11:36.363 --> 11:39.449
My boy. My probably boy.

11:39.908 --> 11:42.035
Okay, when are those
damn DNA results coming?

11:42.035 --> 11:44.496
Jesus...
- Refocus. Mabel.

11:44.496 --> 11:47.207
- Okay, right, yes. Okay. You know,

11:47.207 --> 11:50.210
Mabel did want us to give the knife
to the cops when we first found it.

11:50.210 --> 11:51.712
CHARLES:
You want to give it to Williams?

11:51.712 --> 11:53.714
OLIVER: Well, it doesn't have
Mabel's prints on it, right?

11:53.714 --> 11:55.591
- Unless the killer
did put her prints on it,

11:55.591 --> 11:57.259
hoping we'd give it to the cops.

11:57.259 --> 11:58.510
We need to get rid of it.

11:58.510 --> 12:01.305
- Unless the killer wants us
to get rid of it,

12:01.305 --> 12:03.432
so that he can catch us in
the act of destroying evidence.

12:03.432 --> 12:04.600
[knocking]

12:04.600 --> 12:05.893
- Is everything okay in there?

12:05.893 --> 12:08.061
CHARLES:
Oh, yes! Uh, sorry!

12:08.061 --> 12:09.521
Uh, just a moment.

12:09.521 --> 12:11.440
This turned out to be a two-man job.

12:13.901 --> 12:14.902
[door creaks]

12:16.737 --> 12:18.989
- So you have the knife.

12:19.531 --> 12:22.034
- [innocently]:
Knife? [laughs] Knife...

12:22.910 --> 12:24.077
No.

12:24.077 --> 12:25.370
No knife.
- Stop it!

12:25.370 --> 12:27.331
Do you understand
the definition of perjury?

12:27.331 --> 12:28.749
- I know what perjury is.

12:28.749 --> 12:31.418
I did a production of 12 Angry Men once.

12:31.418 --> 12:33.504
But with women. 12 Angry Women.

12:33.504 --> 12:35.756
One of the sisters
from Hamilton was in it.

12:35.756 --> 12:37.758
This was years before Hamilton.

12:38.717 --> 12:40.302
I know what perjury is.

12:43.096 --> 12:44.389
[quietly]:
I don't.

12:44.389 --> 12:47.392
♪

12:47.392 --> 12:50.395
[seagulls cawing]

12:52.356 --> 12:54.066
[gate squeaking, rattling]

12:59.488 --> 13:02.574
- Any information on who that guy is.
Something to jog my memory.

13:04.201 --> 13:05.410
Yes, it's gone.

13:07.287 --> 13:09.289
Have you ever been to Coney Island?

13:10.415 --> 13:12.000
What'd you do for fun as a kid?

13:14.294 --> 13:18.131
Ah, yes. The adventures of
a teenage grave-robber. Got it.

13:21.593 --> 13:22.636
[clicking]

13:23.595 --> 13:24.972
That's a new way.

13:32.020 --> 13:33.689
How many people work here?

13:33.689 --> 13:35.107
Shit.

13:36.233 --> 13:37.401
Shit, shit, shit, shit.

13:39.027 --> 13:40.279
[knocking]
No,

13:40.279 --> 13:42.656
I need more time with these.
I've got to find this guy.

13:42.656 --> 13:44.992
No! I'm not gonna calm down!

13:44.992 --> 13:46.743
Either the killer is in these files,

13:46.743 --> 13:48.745
or I'm some unhinged psychopath

13:48.745 --> 13:51.415
who goes into fugue states
and stabs people.

13:51.415 --> 13:54.126
Either way, a girl likes to know
these things about herself.

13:55.377 --> 13:56.795
I need a minute.

13:58.297 --> 14:01.216
[door opens, shuts]

14:07.681 --> 14:11.018
[seagulls cawing]

14:12.853 --> 14:14.396
Thank you.

14:14.396 --> 14:16.398
You were just trying to help.

14:16.398 --> 14:17.441
I'm sorry.

14:18.066 --> 14:19.067
[buzz, beep]

14:19.651 --> 14:20.652
[buzz, beep]

14:21.945 --> 14:23.655
[buzz, beep]

14:44.510 --> 14:46.428
[click, machine whirring]

14:46.428 --> 14:47.763
♪ amusement game music ♪

14:47.763 --> 14:49.223
Okay. So,

14:49.223 --> 14:51.850
you've never been to Coney Island,

14:51.850 --> 14:54.102
but have you ever played
Whack-A-Mole?

14:56.104 --> 14:59.274
♪ game dinging ♪

14:59.274 --> 15:00.108
[whacking]

15:03.737 --> 15:05.531
[rapid beeping]

15:07.157 --> 15:08.992
Don't worry, I so get it.

15:09.910 --> 15:12.120
♪ music restarts ♪

15:12.120 --> 15:15.916
[whacking, music fade out]

15:15.916 --> 15:18.085
YOUNG MABEL:
Dad, The X-Files are sick.

15:18.085 --> 15:19.086
♪

15:19.086 --> 15:20.045
[giggles]

15:21.505 --> 15:25.008
[screeching]
[Mabel giggles]

15:25.008 --> 15:27.427
- You know what? You shouldn't be watchi--
- No, no, wait!

15:27.427 --> 15:28.637
This is so awesome.

15:30.013 --> 15:32.140
- Your mother might actually
kill me for this.

15:32.933 --> 15:34.184
[giggles]

15:37.855 --> 15:39.523
I am sorry about today, though.

15:40.440 --> 15:42.568
It's, uh, been a tough month.

15:42.568 --> 15:44.278
This new schedule
they have me on is crazy.

15:44.903 --> 15:47.489
- It's okay.
We can go to the dumb zoo any time.

15:47.948 --> 15:50.492
- It is a good mystery, huh?
[giggles]

15:50.492 --> 15:53.620
And a mystery is just a puzzle,
right, Mabel?

15:53.620 --> 15:56.582
♪ carnival music ♪

15:56.582 --> 15:59.084
[whirring]

16:04.673 --> 16:07.217
- Okay. Six tries is not good.

16:14.224 --> 16:15.475
[laughs]

16:15.475 --> 16:17.769
That's called cheating.
[closes panel]

16:19.646 --> 16:20.772
What'd you get?

16:21.648 --> 16:22.649
[pop]

16:23.108 --> 16:26.361
♪

16:28.405 --> 16:29.698
[music swells]

17:11.240 --> 17:14.785
You know, I can't walk past
the front gate without seeing her body.

17:16.995 --> 17:20.207
I can't walk past Tim's door without...

17:20.207 --> 17:22.292
seeing what he looked like on the floor.

17:22.292 --> 17:25.295
♪

17:25.295 --> 17:28.090
Now, apparently, I'm the kind of person

17:28.090 --> 17:31.218
that could stab someone on the subway
and not even remember.

17:32.344 --> 17:34.179
Which means...

17:34.179 --> 17:37.182
I could also be the sort of person

17:37.182 --> 17:40.978
to put a needle in the chest
of a defenseless old woman.

17:40.978 --> 17:42.354
[echoing laughter]

17:44.273 --> 17:45.482
[gasps]

17:46.733 --> 17:47.776
[grunts]

17:48.986 --> 17:50.487
[Bunny groans]

17:50.487 --> 17:51.321
[thud]

17:52.990 --> 17:55.284
That's what's been scaring me.

17:57.077 --> 17:58.912
It's something that I would do.

18:00.581 --> 18:03.125
I just don't know if I did do it.

18:12.926 --> 18:14.344
[sniffles]

18:14.344 --> 18:16.305
Maybe it's better that way.

18:16.305 --> 18:17.931
[buzzing]

18:19.474 --> 18:21.351
[buzz, beep]

18:23.103 --> 18:26.607
I'm gonna go to the bathroom,
and then let's go back to the city.

18:29.776 --> 18:32.779
♪

18:38.285 --> 18:41.288
♪

18:41.914 --> 18:44.458
- When you say "knife,"

18:44.458 --> 18:46.376
what exactly do you mean?

18:46.376 --> 18:47.628
- Alright, stop being dumbasses.

18:47.628 --> 18:50.589
[Keith crying]

18:50.589 --> 18:51.965
Ah, damn it.

18:51.965 --> 18:54.801
[baby talk]
What's wrong, Keefers? You okay?

18:54.801 --> 18:56.762
[crying]
Do you--

18:56.762 --> 19:00.432
Uh, what about-- You want binky?
You want binky?

19:00.432 --> 19:02.267
No? Uh... Oh!

19:02.267 --> 19:04.144
Toy! You want a toy?
[rattling]

19:04.144 --> 19:05.562
- D-do you need a hand?

19:05.562 --> 19:07.356
- Nope. Got it.

19:07.356 --> 19:10.692
- My son Will used to get a tummy ache...

19:10.692 --> 19:12.778
after feeding.

19:12.778 --> 19:14.780
You know, gas bubbles.

19:14.780 --> 19:17.324
[crying continues]

19:17.324 --> 19:19.451
Are you familiar with A Chorus Line?

19:19.451 --> 19:20.994
- Excuse me?
[rattling]

19:20.994 --> 19:23.956
- Here, let me just... Trust me on this.

19:24.748 --> 19:27.668
Okay, we put this down. This is the stage.

19:27.668 --> 19:30.045
And here, give him to me.
- What?

19:30.045 --> 19:32.172
- J-just trust me. Trust me.

19:32.172 --> 19:34.591
[sighs]
I know what I'm doing.

19:34.591 --> 19:36.510
[baby talk]:
Oh no!

19:36.510 --> 19:39.972
Oh, no. Oh, no, look at this.

19:39.972 --> 19:41.139
[crying]

19:41.139 --> 19:42.808
♪ Bum bum bum ♪

19:42.808 --> 19:44.726
♪ One ♪
[imitates drum]

19:45.519 --> 19:47.688
♪ Singular sensation ♪

19:47.688 --> 19:50.732
♪ Every little step he takes ♪

19:50.732 --> 19:53.277
♪ Da da da da da da da da ♪

19:53.277 --> 19:54.987
♪ One smile ♪

19:54.987 --> 19:57.614
♪ And suddenly, nobody else ♪

19:58.407 --> 20:00.158
♪ Will do ♪

20:00.158 --> 20:01.326
[Keith passes gas]
Oh.

20:02.411 --> 20:05.247
[Keith cooing]
Oh, eureka!

20:05.247 --> 20:06.915
[laughing]

20:06.915 --> 20:09.501
And Joy is your new middle name!

20:09.501 --> 20:13.255
Now, that made him happy.

20:13.255 --> 20:15.549
[baby talk]
Oh, yes, yes, yes.

20:15.549 --> 20:18.051
There we go. Look at that.

20:18.051 --> 20:20.470
And we fold up the stage.

20:22.139 --> 20:23.140
Ah!

20:24.141 --> 20:25.726
- I'm never gonna do that.

20:25.726 --> 20:27.519
You have zero dignity.

20:27.519 --> 20:29.771
My baby has zero dignity.
That's not happening.

20:29.771 --> 20:31.231
- Oh, you're going to try this.

20:31.231 --> 20:32.191
I promise.

20:32.191 --> 20:34.526
You'll do anything if you think
it will help your kid.

20:34.526 --> 20:37.154
- Having barely been a parent,
I can say that is true.

20:37.154 --> 20:38.197
WILLIAMS:
Oh...

20:38.822 --> 20:41.158
Which is where you are with your girl.

20:42.034 --> 20:43.535
Guys, just so you know,

20:44.369 --> 20:46.830
I am not trying to put her away.

20:46.830 --> 20:48.624
Okay? So, if she's innocent,

20:49.249 --> 20:52.419
you should help me out.
I just wanna solve this case.

20:56.006 --> 20:57.299
[whispering]

20:57.299 --> 20:58.675
- Yeah. Okay.

21:00.969 --> 21:02.638
- We need to go to the bathroom.

21:04.806 --> 21:07.809
[water running]

21:12.439 --> 21:14.608
♪

21:14.608 --> 21:16.026
[knocking]

21:18.612 --> 21:20.155
- Dad?

21:20.155 --> 21:21.573
- Mabel.

21:21.573 --> 21:23.116
You're not supposed to be here today.

21:23.116 --> 21:24.576
- But look what
I got us for trick-or-treat.

21:24.576 --> 21:26.870
- Mija, I told you.
We're not going trick-or-treating.

21:28.413 --> 21:30.666
If you want to do a puzzle,
I got this new one--

21:31.792 --> 21:33.710
- I don't wanna do another stupid puzzle!

21:33.710 --> 21:35.963
You promised we'd go as Mulder and Scully!

21:35.963 --> 21:38.423
All you do anymore
is break your promises.

21:41.218 --> 21:42.719
- I know I do.

21:44.054 --> 21:45.556
I wish I could keep them.

21:47.558 --> 21:48.892
Especially for you.

21:48.892 --> 21:51.895
♪

21:52.980 --> 21:55.482
[water dripping]

21:55.482 --> 21:56.567
[baby fussing]

21:56.567 --> 21:58.777
- This is so crazy!
Look what we just found...

21:58.777 --> 21:59.862
- ...behind the toilet.
- In the ceiling.

21:59.862 --> 22:01.238
- In the ceiling.
- Behind the toilet.

22:01.238 --> 22:04.449
- Okay, I love cringe comedy,
but this is painful to watch.

22:09.454 --> 22:10.747
The knife.

22:11.373 --> 22:13.917
- Oh, is it?
WILLIAMS: I get it.

22:13.917 --> 22:16.420
You don't know where this came from.
I got you.

22:16.420 --> 22:19.882
- Whatever it is, you'll find it doesn't
have Mabel's prints on it.

22:19.882 --> 22:22.050
- We hope.
OLIVER: My prints are on the knife,

22:22.050 --> 22:23.719
but that's just because it belongs to me

22:23.719 --> 22:25.012
and it was stolen from my apartment

22:25.012 --> 22:26.388
because we're being framed.

22:26.388 --> 22:28.432
You must see that
kind of thing all the time.

22:28.432 --> 22:30.726
- The prints of my teenage
somewhat-stepdaughter Lucy

22:30.726 --> 22:32.895
are on it, too,
although she is uninvolved.

22:32.895 --> 22:34.897
- Okay. Okay.

22:34.897 --> 22:37.232
Got it. And thank you.

22:37.232 --> 22:38.233
Seriously, thank you.

22:38.233 --> 22:40.485
I'll let you know what I find.

22:41.695 --> 22:44.114
[belting]
♪ Do... I... ♪

22:44.114 --> 22:46.533
♪ Really have to mention ♪

22:46.533 --> 22:48.785
♪ He's... ♪

22:48.785 --> 22:50.787
♪ The... ♪

22:50.787 --> 22:52.789
♪ One! ♪

22:53.582 --> 22:56.168
Like I don't fucking know Chorus Line.

22:56.168 --> 22:58.378
[laughing]
[door opens]

22:59.338 --> 23:00.672
- That's hilarious.
[door shuts]

23:00.672 --> 23:02.633
[water running]

23:02.633 --> 23:04.510
[water stops]

23:04.510 --> 23:06.678
[draining]

23:07.429 --> 23:10.432
♪

23:20.776 --> 23:23.111
[gurgling]

23:26.698 --> 23:29.034
[door opens, shuts]

23:46.552 --> 23:47.928
[pulls off bandage]

23:54.059 --> 23:54.893
[bangs locker]

24:17.666 --> 24:18.750
[bang]

24:19.251 --> 24:20.210
[opens locker]

24:21.295 --> 24:22.296
[slams locker]

24:27.009 --> 24:28.260
[bang]
[man grunts]

24:28.260 --> 24:31.555
♪

24:37.561 --> 24:38.520
- Theo!

24:39.021 --> 24:40.564
Oh! Come on!

24:49.323 --> 24:51.700
We have to go. Get to the car, okay?

24:57.623 --> 25:00.417
[car rumbling]
[distant siren]

25:02.419 --> 25:04.755
[sighs] Ew...

25:06.381 --> 25:08.383
Oh, thank God!

25:10.260 --> 25:12.095
Wait. Where's the matchbook?

25:12.930 --> 25:15.933
Damn it! He has the matchbook!

25:16.767 --> 25:17.768
[sighs]

25:18.644 --> 25:21.772
[sighs] Well, that seems about right.

25:22.773 --> 25:23.941
They're at the diner.

25:28.654 --> 25:30.155
Oh my god.

25:31.990 --> 25:35.077
We need--
We need to get back. Right now.

25:35.077 --> 25:36.495
[ringing]

25:38.372 --> 25:39.414
[ringing]

25:41.667 --> 25:42.918
[ringing, hangs up]

25:43.877 --> 25:45.379
[sighs]

25:45.379 --> 25:47.756
♪

25:48.590 --> 25:50.676
My dad died when I was 7.

25:52.094 --> 25:54.680
They didn't tell me
what was really happening.

25:57.307 --> 25:59.351
They wanted to protect me.

25:59.351 --> 26:02.604
[EKG beeping]
[respirator hissing]

26:02.604 --> 26:03.772
Dad?

26:04.398 --> 26:05.774
He said...

26:05.774 --> 26:08.277
he had to move out for work.

26:08.277 --> 26:10.946
Six months later, he was dead.

26:10.946 --> 26:12.447
Stomach cancer.

26:12.906 --> 26:15.367
I knew something wasn't right,

26:15.367 --> 26:17.870
but I was happy to play along.

26:18.745 --> 26:21.790
[beeping, hissing]
I didn't know how to cope

26:21.790 --> 26:24.793
with him dying, so I didn't.

26:30.757 --> 26:33.760
Instead, I flipped the pieces
over in my mind

26:33.760 --> 26:36.263
until I couldn't see
the image anymore.

26:38.140 --> 26:39.975
Just like he'd shown me.

26:39.975 --> 26:42.436
♪

26:42.436 --> 26:45.480
That was when I lost
my first memory.

26:48.066 --> 26:50.068
And it's happened since.

26:51.236 --> 26:53.280
♪ dramatic music ♪

26:53.280 --> 26:56.909
If something was too much
or too difficult.

26:58.952 --> 27:01.246
When I was afraid to see
what really happened

27:03.123 --> 27:05.125
or what I had possibly done.

27:08.253 --> 27:10.756
But, I have to flip the pieces now.

27:15.344 --> 27:16.887
All of them.

27:18.805 --> 27:21.808
Otherwise,
I'll never see the full picture.

27:21.808 --> 27:24.728
[beeping, hissing]

27:26.980 --> 27:29.983
♪

27:33.529 --> 27:36.114
[beeping, hissing]

27:48.502 --> 27:51.004
[door opens]
[muffled laughter]

27:51.004 --> 27:52.005
[door shuts]

27:55.384 --> 27:57.511
[footsteps]
[door creaks]

27:57.511 --> 27:58.887
[door shuts]
[gasps]

28:01.640 --> 28:02.516
Oh!

28:04.560 --> 28:05.853
Bunny...

28:08.689 --> 28:09.940
No, no, no, no, no...

28:11.316 --> 28:12.568
[thudding]

28:16.488 --> 28:17.739
It's not my fault.

28:19.032 --> 28:20.868
I didn't stab her.

28:23.871 --> 28:26.290
♪

28:28.584 --> 28:31.587
[street noise, chatter]

28:36.175 --> 28:38.302
[inaudible]

28:39.928 --> 28:40.929
[sighs]

28:41.847 --> 28:43.849
[undoes seatbelt]

28:44.474 --> 28:46.101
Well, thank you.

28:59.448 --> 29:01.283
[laughs] Was that right?

29:07.789 --> 29:09.708
I was wrong about you.

29:11.460 --> 29:15.255
And I don't know everything
that's going on with you,

29:16.507 --> 29:18.884
but pushing things away?

29:20.385 --> 29:22.262
It's never really worked for me.

29:26.558 --> 29:27.809
[opens car door]

29:30.479 --> 29:31.480
[shuts car door]

29:32.064 --> 29:34.358
♪ soft music playing ♪

29:34.358 --> 29:36.735
Hey!
- Oh my god.

29:38.195 --> 29:39.363
Oh!

29:40.656 --> 29:44.326
[audio muffled]

29:58.131 --> 30:01.134
[muffled audio continues]

30:06.515 --> 30:07.558
[muffled ringing]

30:08.684 --> 30:10.727
[muffled answer]
[muffled response]

30:14.064 --> 30:15.566
- Thank you.

30:16.400 --> 30:17.693
So, Charles...

30:19.027 --> 30:21.613
This isn't good, what I'm about to say,

30:21.613 --> 30:23.198
okay?

30:25.117 --> 30:27.578
When I found that Glitter Guy,

30:27.578 --> 30:29.621
he had this on him.

30:41.175 --> 30:42.176
[ringing]

30:42.176 --> 30:43.427
- Jesus.

30:43.427 --> 30:45.053
Come on, Lucy, answer.

30:45.053 --> 30:46.054
[ringing]

30:47.055 --> 30:49.141
- Hey. Where are you?
- Lucy! Where are you?

30:49.141 --> 30:50.517
- I'm at your place.
- Listen, you need--

30:50.517 --> 30:52.519
- I came to see y--
[clang, power whirring down]

30:54.062 --> 30:56.690
- Lucy? Lucy!
[dropped call beeping]

30:56.690 --> 30:58.650
- Maybe the call dropped.

30:58.650 --> 30:59.902
- Oh, I know this.

30:59.902 --> 31:02.905
♪

31:02.905 --> 31:04.406
[distant siren]

31:04.907 --> 31:06.909
We've got a blackout, people.

31:11.830 --> 31:14.833
♪

31:14.833 --> 31:17.836
[siren fades out]
